:<math>
\begin{align}
\frac{\mbox{d}\ln x}{\mbox{d}x} &= \lim_{h \to 0} \frac{\ln (x + h) - \ln x}{h} \\
&= \lim_{h \to 0} (\frac{1}{h} \ln (\frac{x + h}{x})) \\
&= \lim_{h \to 0} (\frac{x}{xh} \ln (1 + \frac{h}{x})) \\
&= \frac{1}{x} \ln ( \lim_{h \to 0} (1 + \frac{h}{x})^{\frac{x}{h}}) \\
&= \frac{1}{x} \ln e \\
&= \frac{1}{x}
\end{align}
</math>

